    march_ch1_title: "Technology & City Life",
    march_ch1_count: "Six Ideas",
    march_idea1_title: "Ground that produces electricity.",
    march_idea1_body: "Piezoelectric paving slabs convert kinetic energy into electricity. A subway station with fifty thousand passengers a day covers its lighting needs this way — no solar, no cable, no new infrastructure. Pavegen runs active installations in London, Paris and Dubai.",
    march_idea2_title: "Paths that light themselves.",
    march_idea2_body: "Studio Roosegaarde built the world's first self-luminous bike path in 2014: 500 metres of paving with no power connection, still operating today. The principle is trivially scalable — every road-surface tender could include it.",
    march_idea3_title: "Shade as infrastructure.",
    march_idea3_body: "In 2023 Seville fitted central streets with shade structures and cooling sprayers. Measured impact: up to five degrees temperature reduction, thirty percent more pedestrian footfall in summer. A template for any Mediterranean city.",
    march_idea3_source: "City of Seville",
    march_idea4_title: "Repair is cheaper than buying new.",
    march_idea4_body: "The EU Right to Repair (April 2024) obliges manufacturers, for the first time, to make spare parts available. Next step: 0 % VAT on repair services, a levy on premature disposal. System design beats appeals.",
    march_idea4_source: "European Commission · Right to Repair",
    march_idea5_title: "Your city pays you a dividend.",
    march_idea5_body: "Cities sell anonymised usage and traffic data to research and companies. Amsterdam is piloting models that distribute the proceeds directly to citizens. Data sovereignty becomes a property right — not just a privacy topic.",
    march_idea6_title: "Buildings that produce food.",
    march_idea6_body: "The BIQ House in Hamburg has run the first urban algae façade at scale since 2013. Biomass for heating and hot water, plus thermal insulation — at costs comparable to conventional façades. Not a prototype: in operation for over ten years.",
    march_ch2_title: "Education & Infrastructure",
    march_ch2_count: "Three Ideas",
    march_idea7_title: "Europe as one single campus.",
    march_idea7_body: "Erasmus+ has given thirteen million people cross-border educational experiences — limited to academic contexts. A universal recognition infrastructure would include vocational training, certificates and practical experience. The train becomes the campus.",
    march_idea8_title: "Qualifications that count everywhere — instantly.",
    march_idea8_body: "A Polish nursing professional waits six to twelve months today for recognition in Portugal — with identical training standards. AI-based qualification translation solves the structural problem in real time: no paperwork, no translation costs.",
    march_idea8_source: "EU · Professional Qualifications",
    march_idea9_title: "Urban motorways become food forests.",
    march_idea9_body: "Rotterdam has converted three kilometres of former inner-city motorway into public green space. The Voedselbos Almere produces food on previously sealed surface. The principle: heavy traffic underground or relocated — surface released.",
    march_ch3_title: "Power, Growth & Democracy",
    march_ch3_count: "Four Ideas",
    march_idea10_title: "Europe as a third world power — without a Washington mandate.",
    march_idea10_body: "Beside the US and China there is a third option: a sovereign EU that coordinates militarily, leads technologically and acts economically independently. The infrastructure exists — from the EDA to the ESM. What's missing isn't money or technology. It's the political will to deploy them.",
    march_idea11_title: "Africa partnership instead of development aid.",
    march_idea11_body: "The Global Gateway Initiative bundles €300 billion for investments in Africa by 2027. Return: long-term supply contracts for critical raw materials. Not a development-aid model — strategic economic access to the world's fastest growing region.",
    march_idea12_title: "Less bureaucracy, more output.",
    march_idea12_body: "Germany lost over 30 % of its solar-module production to China in 2024 — not because of weaker technology but because of four-year approval procedures. Outcome funding instead of input control: four months instead of four years. Smart system architecture, not deregulation.",
    march_idea13_title: "Citizens decide the budget — by lottery.",
    march_idea13_body: "Paris let one hundred and fifty randomly selected citizens decide on climate budgets in 2021. Result: more ambitious measures than parliamentary proposals — seventy percent of them implemented. Representative citizens' assemblies systematically outperform party processes.",
    march_ch4_title: "Tools — public EU data",
    march_ch4_count: "Seven Sources",
    march_ch4_intro: "Everything public, machine-readable, free. With an AI agent these turn into solid analyses, petitions and position papers within hours — no prior knowledge, no budget.",
    march_tool1_desc: "All EU laws in full text. An AI extracts the legal status on your topic and shows which rights are already enforceable today.",
    march_tool2_desc: "All open consultations with deadline. An agent monitors them automatically and flags relevant topics with prepared submission templates.",
    march_tool3_desc: "Full voting history of every MEP. AI generates a personal briefing with concrete arguments based on their own voting record.",
    march_tool4_desc: "All European Citizens' Initiatives, successful and failed. What earned a million signatures, what didn't? Includes a template for your own initiative.",
    march_tool5_desc: "Energy poverty, housing costs, healthcare — by region, year, population group. Your region against the EU average, in seconds.",
    march_tool6_name: "EURES Job Mobility<a href=\"https://eures.europa.eu\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">eures.europa.eu</a>",
    march_tool6_desc: "Bureaucratic requirements for cross-border work in every EU country — with the legal basis for complaints when the single market fails to deliver.",
    march_tool7_desc: "Political positions on EU topics, simply explained and made comparable. The ideal entry point before you take an AI agent into voting histories and legal texts.",
